{
    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix variable name conflicts in F1AP ASN.1 sequence encoding\n\n### Summary\nFixed variable name conflicts in the F1AP library that caused compilation failures when encoding multiple protocol extensions. The issue occurred in functions that add multiple extensions to the same ASN.1 sequence container using the `asn1cSequenceAdd` macro.\n\nWhen both HandoverPreparationInformation and MeasurementTimingConfiguration extensions were present in CU-to-DU RRC information, or when both DL and UL PDCP sequence number length extensions were present in DRB setup, the code would fail to compile due to variable redeclaration errors.\n\n### Changes\n- `openair2/F1AP/lib/f1ap_ue_context.c`: \n  - Fixed `encode_cu_to_du_rrc_info` function to use unique variable names (`ie_ext_ho`, `ie_ext_mtc`) for each extension\n  - Fixed DRB setup functions to use unique variable names (`ext_ie_dl`, `ext_ie_ul`) for PDCP extensions\n  - Applied same fixes to DRB modification functions\n\n"
}